The Klaviyo MCP server is a tool that allows AI platforms, such as Claude and Cursor, to securely connect with your Klaviyo data to perform tasks like reporting, campaign creation, and segment analysis [1][2][3].

For most users, the recommended approach is the remote-hosted server, which uses the URL https://mcp.klaviyo.com/mcp [1][4]. To configure this in a client like Cursor, add the following to your MCP server settings [1][5]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "klaviyo": {
      "url": "https://mcp.klaviyo.com/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

You can control server behavior using query parameters like read-only=true to disable write actions [1][4]. For local installations, you will need the uv package manager and a private API key with the appropriate scope permissions [6][4][5].
